oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Battleship Maine gun mount front view, circa 1930s
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Lamb, Herman
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black-and-white photograph of a gun mount and shield from the Battleship Maine located on Lee Highway in Chattanooga, Tennessee. The Battleship Maine was an American naval ship that sank in the Havana Harbor in 1898 during Cuba's revolt against Spain. It was recovered in 1912 and various memorials were placed throughout the United States.
